(0000000400, 0000000025, 0000000003, 0000000001, 'Each view can be customized by adding a specific css and/or javascript file.\r\nEvery page that makes use of a view where a css or javascript file is specified automatically adds these files to the html header.\r\nThis is accomplished by overwriting the methods [`BaseView::get_css_inludes`](https://selfhelp.psy.unibe.ch/demo/doc/doxygen/html/classBaseView.html#a26d6d3eaea3a57fc702a95474c7230cb) and [`BaseView::get_js_inludes`](https://selfhelp.psy.unibe.ch/demo/doc/doxygen/html/classBaseView.html#a0272ac3735f12152a79db2f44f0b2cf6), respecively.\r\n\r\nFor example, to add a css file `myStyle.css` to the view of style `myStyle`, one would add the following lines to the class `MyStyleView`:\r\n```php\r\npublic function get_css_includes($local = array())\r\n{\r\n    $local = array(__DIR__ . \"/myStyle.css\");\r\n    return parent::get_css_includes($local);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nTo add a javascript file `myStyle.js` to the view of style `myStyle`, one would add the following lines to the class `MyStyleView`:\r\n```php\r\npublic function get_js_includes($local = array())\r\n{\r\n    $local = array(__DIR__ . \"/myStyle.js\");\r\n    return parent::get_js_includes($local);\r\n}\r\n```'),
